	<section id="overview">
	<title>Overview</title>
	<p>CILib (Computational Intelligence Library) is a collaborative framework for developing <a href="http://www.worldscinet.com/ijcia/ijcia.shtml">Computational Intelligence</a>
	software in:</p>
	<ul>
	<li>Swarm Intelligence</li>
	<li>Evolutionary Computation</li>
	<li>Neural Networks</li>
	<li>Artifical Immune Systems</li>
	<li>Fuzzy Logic</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
	CILib is maintained by the <a href="http://cirg.cs.up.ac.za/">Computational Intelligence Reasearch Group</a> hosted by the <a href="http://www.cs.up.ac.za/">Department of Computer Science</a>
	at the <a href="http://www.up.ac.za">University of Pretoria</a> in <a href="http://www.southafrica.net/">South Africa</a>.
	</p>
	</section>
